UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'The article "The Power of Play: How Games Can Help Children Learn" describes the benefits of incorporating games into education.  The author explains that games are not merely a fun distraction, but can be a powerful tool for stimulating children''s cognitive development and fostering their social and emotional growth.  This is accomplished through the integration of game-based learning techniques that create engaging and interactive learning experiences for students.  The author cites a number of studies that demonstrate the effectiveness of games in promoting learning outcomes.  For example, the article highlights a study in which elementary school students who played a game designed to teach them about fractions showed significant improvement in their understanding of fractions compared to students who did not play the game.  The author concludes that games are a valuable asset in education, and that educators should embrace game-based learning techniques in order to provide a more engaging and effective learning experience for students.',
